This paper deals with the development of affect-aware conversational agents, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of probabilistic models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of Affect Control Theory in Human-Computer Interaction suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the development of neural dialogue systems, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
